&lt;/div&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kansai" /><category term="Cherry Blossoms" /><category term="Rivers" /><category term="Night" /><category term="Lightup" /><summary type="html">Went for a walk in Yamato-Takada, south of Nara. The cherry trees are illuminated along the Takada river and the warmer weather made for a nice evening.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2203_A7R06374-HDR.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2203_A7R06374-HDR.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Osawa Pond・大沢池</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220329/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Osawa Pond・大沢池" /><published>2022-03-29T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-03-29T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/osawa</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220329/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    Cherry blossoms are coming out at Osawa Pond, part of Daikakuji Temple.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
   大覚寺の大沢池に桜が咲いています。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Cherry Blossoms" /><category term="Ponds" /><summary type="html">Cherry blossoms are coming out at Osawa Pond, part of Daikakuji Temple.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2203_A7R06278.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2203_A7R06278.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kyoto Gosho・京都御所</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220328/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kyoto Gosho・京都御所" /><published>2022-03-28T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-03-28T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/gyoen</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220328/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    There are several large, well-known, weeping cherry trees in the Kyoto Imperial Palace Park. This is a single branch of the &lt;em&gt;Konoe no Shidarae Zakura&lt;/em&gt;, which translates as The Imperial Guards Weeping Cherry Tree. It sits next to a creek with a bridge in the distance. I like how the dark background makes the cherry blossoms stand out.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
   Below, several other photos from Kyoto Gosho.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
   京都御所公園には、有名なしだれ桜の大木が何本かある。これは「近衛のしだれ桜」です。小川のほとりにあり、遠くに橋がかかっています。背景の水が桜を引き立てているのがいいですね。
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;
   以下、京都御所での他の写真数点。
&lt;/p&gt;
